Description: Papyrus. Demotic narrative text. Recto; two columns, both torn at the bottom; top margins preserved. Column 1: 16+x lines of text (beginning of each line in lacuna); Column 2: beginnings of 17+x lines. Verso; two columns. Column 1: ends of 17+x lines of text; Column 2: 21+x incomplete lines. Part of the Petubastis Cycle.
Curator's comments: Bibliography Martin, C.J. 2016-2017. The Michaelides Demotic Material, Enchoria 35: 1-8.
Published by E. Bresciani, 'Testi demotici nella Collezione Michaelidis' (= Oriens Antiquus 2), Rome, 1963, text II, pp. 4-8, pl. ii-iii.
